        "section_value": "Chief Complaint\nLeft shoulder pain.\nHistory of Present Illness\nThe patient reports left shoulder pain over the past six weeks, exacerbated by overhead activities and lying on the affected side. He denies recent trauma and reports partial relief with acetaminophen. He has been doing stair workouts. The patient denies swelling in their legs and pins and needles.\nFindings\nExamination reveals reduced active abduction of the left shoulder and pain with impingement testing. The patient reports high blood pressure.\nAssessment\nThe patient has joint pain. The patient reports pain.\nPlan\nThe doctor ordered a physical therapy referral. The doctor ordered an autoimmune profile. The doctor ordered a lipid profile. The patient is taking norvasc at a dosage of 5 mg per day. The doctor continued the patient on metformin 500 mg twice a day. The doctor ordered meloxicam 15 mg once a day. The doctor ordered a physical therapy referral.",
